>>286697269
Yeah there's not really "healer gear" anymore and in a lot of cases there's not really spec gear. Spirit isn't a thing anymore so for the most part any piece of gear you get for your druid is probably BiS for most of your specs provided it's an upgrade. Furthermore for the classes like shaman or druid who have specs that want different mainstat your gear automatically swaps from it having like 300+ agi to 300+ int. There's no longer like int mail there's just mail gear and so on.

With gearing as it is, for the most part, outside of some very specific sidegrade examples your gear set for one spec is probably the exact same for the the other minus trinkets (which still maintain a level of specificity in what they do) and for some classes weapons. Taking druid as the example here your BiS is literally the exact same for every slot minus swapping out trinkets.

So yeah, as leveling you just play as balance (or feral if you want) and then you just swap to resto when you get in a dungeon. It's a press of a button for retail.

>>286697173
What makes you say that? It seems like he did a pretty good job if he could make all the games that he has. compared to most directors he's easily neck and shoulder above the rest.

>>286697485
All of the previous games stink heavily of direction change and re-purposed assets. If you ever watch any of Lance's videos, you'll see that Ebrietas used to be a Moon Presence tier entity and not just an optional boss they stuck into UCW as an afterthought, among other things. It gets worse when you go even further back and look at things like Priscilla's original role in Dark Souls 1, the unfinished Undead King Jar-Eel, the ceremonies system in Dark Souls 3, and so on.

Basically, Miyazaki just has the staff make levels and assets willy-nilly and then shoehorns them in here and there to make the game work. There's no unified grand vision from start to finish, up until Sekiro, where he states in the interviews that the game actually ended up mostly complete to specs without trashing too much shit. It's also the same reason why he had to ask George R. R. Martin to write the lore for Elden Ring, so that he could actually make the world feel like an actual world instead of just putting random shit here and there and connecting them together with bread crumb item descriptions.
